    <thetext>Description of problem:
After updating to firefox-48.0-5.fc25, launching firefox freezes a GNOME on Wayland virtual-guest session.

Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
gnome-shell-3.21.4-1.fc25

How reproducible:
Always

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Start a GNOME on Wayland virtual-guest session.
2. Launch firefox

Actual results:
Desktop is frozen, no reaction to keyboard or mouse; even switching to a virtual console by means of gnome-boxes&apos; keyboard button is ineffective.

Expected results:
Firefox starts up as expected.

Additional info:
- Firefox 47.0.x used to work as expected since upgrading to Xorg 1.18.4.
- Installed packages include:
  * firefox-48.0-5.fc25
  * mutter-3.21.4-1.fc25
  * xorg-x11-server-Xwayland-1.18.4-1.fc25
- firefox-48.0-5.fc25 works as expected in a GNOME on Xorg virtual-guest session.
- GNOME Web (epiphany) works expected in a GNOME on Wayland virtual-guest session.</thetext>
